instruction:
In the class, there are 30 children. One-third of all the children are girls.

Create a variable `kids` with a value of 30.
Create a variable `girls` in which you calculate the number of girls in the class.
Create a variable `boys` in which you calculate the number of boys in the class.

Here is an example that is fundamentally similar to what needs to be done, but adapt it to the task requirements:
```javascript
const a = 30;
const b = a / 3;
const c = a - b ;
```

hint:
```javascript
const kids = 30;
const girls = kids / 3;
const boys = kids - girls;
```
